      "description": "CFD-predicted NIH compared against in-vitro measurement at 4 L/min, 3500 RPM — a high-shear operating point representative of peak VAD demand. Predicted NIH = 0.0071 g/100L; measured NIH = 0.0068 ± 0.0007 g/100L. Relative error 4.4%. The validation report notes that aleatory variability in blood rheology and pump manufacturing tolerances contributes to scatter at this operating point. Uncertainty is addressed narratively; the credibility team judged the agreement acceptable given the tight relative error, but no Monte Carlo or interval-based UQ artifact was formally registered for this result."
